luding Homebrew, Wine, and all the other programs Homebrew installed to get Wine to work correctly.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.davidbaumgold.com/tutorials/wine-mac/#uninstalling-wine-and-homebrew\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davidbaumgold.com%2Ftutorials%2Fwine-mac%2F%23uninstalling-wine-and-homebrew&d=xCoCf8VsiGpfeKn2W5Kz0jCdMQr7etzq9tFbjrA%2B72k%3D&h=8286e011\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.davidbaumgold.com/tutorials/wine-mac/#uninstalling-wine-and-homebrew</a>"},{"pid":"c32e9b0f555e9ab65692984dc888b051cf6c2112","tid":738803,"uid":32753,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"0075d497b6eec3f1574fa39b8dd2daf1981fb4cc","tid":738803,"uid":28563,"like":22,"dislike":0,"score":22,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-07-11T20:12:46.000Z","msg":"Uninstalling Wine and Homebrew<br />\n<br />\nIf you try Wine and you don't like it, uninstalling it is easy. Just run this command:<br />\n<br />\nbrew uninstall wine<br />\n<br />\nAnd Homebrew will helpfully remove Wine from your computer. However, in order to install Wine, Homebrew also had to install many other small programs that Wine relies upon to work correctly. (That's why the install process takes so long!) If you want to remove these as well, run this script:<br />\n<br />\nruby -e &quot;$(curl -fsSL <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/uninstall\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2FHomebrew%2Finstall%2Fmaster%2Funinstall&d=xCoCf8VsiGpfeKn2W5Kz0jCdMQr7etzq9tFbjrA%2B72k%3D&h=70d43e97\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/uninstall</a>)&quot;<br />\n<br />\nThat script will remove everthing that you installed in this tutorial, including Homebrew, Wine, and all the other programs Homebrew installed to get Wine to work correctly.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.davidbaumgold.com/tutorials/wine-mac/#uninstalling-wine-and-homebrew\" data-sr-url=\